The paper deals with outlier detection in traffic data using statistical methods such as Naive Bayes and Gaussian Mixture Model. This involves data analysis, machine learning, and computer vision techniques, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper involves the use of statistical models and algorithms, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
